use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yms1665702709648.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yms1665702709648.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yms1665702709648.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yms1665702709648\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Severity\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Severity level of the message. Valid values are <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">None</code> (default), <code class=\"ph codeph\">Informational</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Warning</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">Error</code>, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">Serious error</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yms1665702709648__section_ahw_gjr_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d447225e66\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yms1665702709648__p_d110372e1_d110373e1_d110374e1\">Many message objects are used to define the text of\n        labels and menus, in which case setting the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Severity</span> is not\n        desirable.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yms1665702709648__p_d110375e1_d110376e1_d110377e1\">For error and warning messages that are displayed in\n        response to an event or action, it may be desirable to set the\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Severity</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yms1665702709648__p_d110378e1_d110379e1_d110380e1\">Depending on the platform, the\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Severity</span> property determines the type of audio signal, or beep,\n        produced when the message is displayed. This value can be overridden by the\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess/nobeep</span> ProcScript statement.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yms1665702709648__section_w1v_hjr_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d447225e93\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"yms1665702709648__ul_z41_jjr_cxb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yms1665702709648__li_d42680e1_d42681e1_d42682e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pdp1665702709496.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pdp1665702709496.html\" title=\"A Message is a Development Object that defines text to be used in the application, such as a label, help text, prompt, or error message.\">Message</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hir1705568318852.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Messages</a><p>Messages are language-related objects that enable you to deploy a Uniface application in different languages and locales. They are stored in language-specific libraries, and Uniface automatically chooses the appropriate library at runtime based on the configuration.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mae1719381665957.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>askmess</a><p>Display a message and wait for the user's response.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617195\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617195\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Severity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Severity Severity level of the message. Valid values are None (default), Informational , Warning , Error , or Serious error . Description Many message objects are used to define the text of labels and menus, in which case setting the Severity is not desirable. For error and warning messages that are displayed in response to an event or action, it may be desirable to set the Severity . Depending on the platform, the Severity property determines the type of audio signal, or beep, produced when the message is displayed. This value can be overridden by the askmess/nobeep ProcScript statement. Applies To Message Related Links Messages Messages are language-related objects that enable you to deploy a Uniface application in different languages and locales. They are stored in language-specific libraries, and Uniface automatically chooses the appropriate library at runtime based on the configuration. askmess Display a message and wait for the user's response. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}